<HEAD>Truck Collides With School Bus, 1 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROSENBERG, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A pickup truck collided head-on with a school bus carrying students from a county fair Saturday, critically injuring the truck driver. Twenty students and a teacher were sent to a hospital for observation. The students and teacher were treated and released from a local hospital. The 29-year-old truck driver was flown by helicopter to an emergency room. The students had participated in the livestock competition at the <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bend </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Fair </LOCATION> near <LOCATION> Rosenberg </LOCATION>, 10 miles southwest of <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION>. The southbound truck drove into the northbound lane, striking the bus, as the two vehicles rounded a curve, <PERSON> Rosenberg </PERSON> Police Sgt. <PERSON> Beverly </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> said.
